{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κιρνάω</b> <br /> and <b>κῑονό-ημι</b>, collateral, especially <i>poetry</i>, forms of κεράννυμι, only <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>:— <b>mix</b> wine with water, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus only in 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”, μελίφρονα οἶνον ἐκίρνα (_imperfect_ of κιρνάω) 7.182, 10.356; κίρνη μελιηδέα οἶνον (_imperfect_ of κίρνημι) 14.78, 16.52; κιρνὰς αἴθοπα οἶνον (_participle_) 16.14 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; κιρνᾷ (variant{κίρναται}) κρητῆρα οἴνου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.66; κρατῆρα μελέων κίρναμεν 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 6(5).3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κόμπον κιρνάμεν <b>to mix the cup</b> of praise [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 5(4).25: \">Refs</a>]<i>infinitive</i> κιρνάναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “γυναικεῖα” 2.113 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>participle</i>, κιρνάντες πόλιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 683 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Aeolic dialect</i> κίρναις (ἐγ-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 34 codices (perhaps κέρναις); κιρνῶντες 2nd c.AD: Herodianus Grammaticus 8.4.9 \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i>, ἐκίρνη φάρμακον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Μιθριδάτειος” 111 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, ἴσον ἴσῳ κίρνασθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 10.426b; κιρνᾶται [prev. author] 11.476a, 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Pronominibus;” 74.7, κίρναται “Comica Adespota” 373; χθὼν δὲ πᾶσα καὶ θάλασσα κίρναται τεὰν χάριν “IG” 42(1).130.23 (Epid.)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <i>participle</i> κιρνάμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 3.78: \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>imperfect</i> ἐκίρνατο (ἐν-) [<a href=\"j